<h1>Problem 2224 - 2024 Israel TST, Test 1 P3 of 3, N</h1>
<h2 class='difficulty'>Difficulty: 8</h2>
<p>Let \(n\) be a positive integer and \(p\) be a prime number of the form \(8k+5\). A polynomial \(Q\) of degree at most \(2023\) and nonnegative integer coefficients less than or equal to \(n\) will be called ``cool&#x27;&#x27; if
\[p\mid Q(2)\cdot Q(3) \cdot \ldots \cdot Q(p-2)-1.\]Prove that the number of cool polynomials is even.</p>
